ly registers these classes and methods. I could add a public static getInstance(Object) to ItsUtilsAnonymous1Test and pass ItsUtilsAnonymous1Test.class. Even though the class is in a test package that may be excluded by a filter for agent metadata, JUnit's native reflection config might still make getMethod accessible. However, I wonder if coverage will be affected by the filter?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking metadata and tests**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the tests, which include `bcutil`, and maybe transitive `bcprov` with metadata. It looks like the metadata repository has `org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on`. I should check into that to ensure I'm getting accurate information. So, I need to verify that the setup is correct and that all required components are present in the metadata repo. This will help ensure everything functions as expected.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_vV0mmveErguKUIzD7kty8zNZ|fc_0fdae1f3b7cf2e3e016a25dc476c208197aee8445980c00ac0", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata/org.bouncycastle -maxdepth 3 -name reachability-metadata.json -print | head -20; find metadata/org.bouncycastle -path '*bcprov*reachability-metadata.json' -print | head -10"}, "partialJson": "{\"command\":\"find metadata/org.bouncycastle -maxdepth 3 -name reachability-metadata.json -print | head -20; find metadata/org.bouncycastle -path '*bcprov*reachability-metadata.json' -print | head -10\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1136, "output": 2414, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41438, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780866059960, "responseId": "resp_0fdae1f3b7cf2e3e016a25dc0cfb7c8197b339ec9f4481caf2"}}
